    <h3 class="title">Note</h3>
			
			<li class="footnote " id="-91911_000_041"><a name="-91911_000_041">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote1-91911_000_041">1.</a>
      </span>
				<p>I am aware of Abigail Adams&rsquo;s correspondence with John Adams on this point. However, it does not follow that all of the fifty-six signers of the Declaration were of the same view. Subsequent generations have regarded <span class="emphasis">men</span> in its generic sense. I might have used various other examples on which there could be no question.</p>
